1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:37,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,186 --> 00:00:40,786
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,786 --> 00:00:42,196
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:44,626 --> 00:00:45,666
Hello.

5
00:00:47,696 --> 00:00:48,696
Do you know me?

6
00:00:49,966 --> 00:00:51,196
You're CEO Mari Yoon.

7
00:00:53,606 --> 00:00:56,606
Is it true
you made a lobbyist offer to Belen?

8
00:00:58,336 --> 00:00:59,476
I'm not recording.

9
00:00:59,946 --> 00:01:01,846
Without your consent,
I won't release it either.

10
00:01:01,846 --> 00:01:02,976
How did you find out?

11
00:01:03,776 --> 00:01:05,046
Did someone at the hotel leak this?

12
00:01:05,046 --> 00:01:06,286
Absolutely not.

13
00:01:09,586 --> 00:01:11,586
The rumor that Lee Woo Seul is your son.

14
00:01:15,556 --> 00:01:16,726
Have you heard it?

15
00:01:18,596 --> 00:01:19,596
That's ridiculous.

16
00:01:20,096 --> 00:01:21,326
This is the first I'm hearing of it.

17
00:01:21,326 --> 00:01:22,966
That's why I'm asking.

18
00:01:23,636 --> 00:01:25,096
Someone gave me a tip.

19
00:01:25,096 --> 00:01:26,506
What are you trying to confirm?

20
00:01:27,006 --> 00:01:28,206
Belen? Lee Woo Seul?

21
00:01:28,406 --> 00:01:29,636
What publication are you from?

22
00:01:29,636 --> 00:01:30,706
Sungwoo Daily.

23
00:01:30,936 --> 00:01:32,646
I'm Geum Ba Ra from the culture desk.

24
00:01:33,476 --> 00:01:35,246
I've also covered Lee Woo Seul.

25
00:01:36,576 --> 00:01:38,546
Did you happen to see the article?

26
00:01:38,546 --> 00:01:40,446
It's not like I even live in Korea.

27
00:01:40,986 --> 00:01:43,316
How is Director Park Sang Jik doing?

28
00:01:44,586 --> 00:01:46,186
He retired last week.

29
00:01:46,786 --> 00:01:48,786
He had some health issues.

30
00:01:48,786 --> 00:01:49,896
What's wrong?

31
00:01:59,666 --> 00:02:00,766
Ms. Yoon?

32
00:02:13,746 --> 00:02:14,746
Are you all right?

33
00:02:16,786 --> 00:02:17,916
You're a reporter from where again?

34
00:02:18,686 --> 00:02:20,126
Geum Ba Ra from Sungwoo Daily.

35
00:02:22,256 --> 00:02:23,456
What were we talking about?

36
00:02:26,226 --> 00:02:27,826
She's old enough to have already left
the orphanage,

37
00:02:27,826 --> 00:02:31,096
so on a hunch,
I searched all the self-reliance centers,

38
00:02:31,236 --> 00:02:33,436
and Kim Jin Ju was the only person
who matched.

39
00:02:33,436 --> 00:02:34,506
A woman?

40
00:02:34,566 --> 00:02:36,336
Yes, and she's exactly 27.

41
00:02:38,776 --> 00:02:39,806
Thank you.

42
00:02:40,506 --> 00:02:41,506
Good work.

43
00:02:45,346 --> 00:02:47,346
Was it because I was thinking
about Momo too much?

44
00:02:48,586 --> 00:02:50,886
But why did CEO Yoon all of a sudden...

45
00:02:51,256 --> 00:02:53,026
How did you score the Mari Yoon interview?

46
00:02:54,626 --> 00:02:55,756
I just got lucky.

47
00:03:00,896 --> 00:03:02,366
(Manager, Self-Reliance Program)

48
00:03:03,796 --> 00:03:05,396
Hello, sir.

49
00:03:05,396 --> 00:03:07,666
- Hey, it's been a while.
- Yes.

50
00:03:08,036 --> 00:03:09,706
You might want to brace yourself for this.

51
00:03:10,776 --> 00:03:13,206
Someone came by asking
for your contact information.

52
00:03:14,046 --> 00:03:16,646
He said you might be
his long-lost daughter.

53
00:03:17,176 --> 00:03:18,216
Who was it?

54
00:03:18,516 --> 00:03:20,216
He said he's lived abroad for a long time,

55
00:03:20,846 --> 00:03:23,316
so you'll have to meet him
to hear the details for yourself.

56
00:03:25,416 --> 00:03:26,486
Should I text you the number?

57
00:03:27,456 --> 00:03:28,456
Yes, please.

58
00:03:28,726 --> 00:03:29,896
He seemed like a nice person.

59
00:03:30,796 --> 00:03:32,726
You can arrange to meet him here
at our office if you want.

60
00:03:33,766 --> 00:03:35,196
Thank you.

61
00:03:43,936 --> 00:03:45,306
- Hi.
- Hi.

62
00:03:45,376 --> 00:03:46,406
Kim Jin Ju!

63
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:49,046
A student with pierced ears?
What's this?

64
00:03:54,346 --> 00:03:55,346
Sir.

65
00:03:58,486 --> 00:04:00,186
Please give me back my earrings.

66
00:04:00,986 --> 00:04:03,696
When I was left at the orphanage,

67
00:04:04,256 --> 00:04:06,366
they said these were in the blanket
I was wrapped in.

68
00:04:07,726 --> 00:04:09,366
If I wear them around,

69
00:04:10,566 --> 00:04:13,866
I was hoping my parents might see them.

70
00:04:14,606 --> 00:04:16,776
That's quite a fantasy you've got there.

71
00:04:17,376 --> 00:04:19,406
If I make an exception for you,
what about the other students?

72
00:04:21,376 --> 00:04:23,146
I'll let it slide just this once.

73
00:04:25,476 --> 00:04:26,816
Even if they did see them,

74
00:04:27,446 --> 00:04:29,786
do you think they'd say
they were the ones who abandoned you,

75
00:04:29,856 --> 00:04:30,916
and it was nice to see you?

76
00:04:32,056 --> 00:04:33,526
And he calls himself a teacher.

77
00:04:34,926 --> 00:04:37,956
I'm jealous.
I don't have anything like that, you know.

78
00:04:40,166 --> 00:04:43,636
I feel like it'd be better
if I at least had a keepsake like that.

79
00:04:45,066 --> 00:04:47,136
I'd feel less like I was just abandoned.

80
00:04:49,236 --> 00:04:51,276
But was there any love in it?

81
00:04:52,506 --> 00:04:53,776
Spicy rice cakes,
blood sausage, fried food...

82
00:04:55,576 --> 00:04:56,716
And add an egg.

83
00:05:06,326 --> 00:05:08,086
This is Kim Jin Ju.

84
00:05:08,726 --> 00:05:10,056
Is now a good time to talk?

85
00:05:14,696 --> 00:05:15,696
Hello?

86
00:05:17,096 --> 00:05:18,366
Is this Kim Jin Ju?

87
00:05:19,036 --> 00:05:20,036
Yes.

88
00:05:20,036 --> 00:05:22,606
Did Kim Min Hyeok, the manager
at the Self-Reliance Center, brief you?

89
00:05:22,676 --> 00:05:23,676
Yes.

90
00:05:23,676 --> 00:05:25,036
Can we meet today?

91
00:05:26,646 --> 00:05:28,676
I get off work late. Is that all right?

92
00:05:28,876 --> 00:05:30,946
That's fine. I don't mind how late.

93
00:05:31,616 --> 00:05:33,586
How about around nine, then?

94
00:05:37,486 --> 00:05:39,086
Where should we meet?

95
00:05:43,526 --> 00:05:45,756
All right, quiet on set, please.
We're about to roll.

96
00:05:47,126 --> 00:05:48,126
All right, ready.

97
00:05:49,936 --> 00:05:50,936
Action!

98
00:05:56,506 --> 00:05:58,576
- Cut! It's no good.
- Let's do it again.

99
00:06:01,946 --> 00:06:03,146
I need to talk to you for a sec.

100
00:06:07,716 --> 00:06:08,716
Are you here for a story?

101
00:06:09,556 --> 00:06:11,856
- Yes.
- My birth father showed up.

102
00:06:12,116 --> 00:06:13,156
He wants to see me.

103
00:06:13,756 --> 00:06:15,826
I'm meeting him
in the Sera Hotel lounge later.

104
00:06:15,826 --> 00:06:18,026
Can you come with me?
I'm too nervous to go alone.

105
00:06:19,696 --> 00:06:21,466
I have an interview
with Jin Yi Han after this.

106
00:06:25,436 --> 00:06:26,806
How did he contact you?

107
00:06:29,406 --> 00:06:30,406
I guess...

108
00:06:32,136 --> 00:06:34,606
all the kids who suffered
because of Ye Jeong...

109
00:06:36,776 --> 00:06:39,846
will say she got what she deserved.

110
00:06:41,016 --> 00:06:43,586
As her mother, I'm to blame too.

111
00:06:44,416 --> 00:06:47,256
If only I'd known
how she was behaving at school,

112
00:06:48,126 --> 00:06:51,796
I would've met with the kids she hurt,
even belatedly, and apologized.

113
00:06:52,666 --> 00:06:56,196
I should've tried to make it up to them,
but I didn't.

114
00:06:57,736 --> 00:06:59,636
But it's too late for regrets now.

115
00:07:00,236 --> 00:07:02,976
I don't know what to say.

116
00:07:05,576 --> 00:07:07,076
I feel terrible about it too.

117
00:07:08,846 --> 00:07:09,946
It must be karma.

118
00:07:11,576 --> 00:07:13,686
They say you reap what you sow,

119
00:07:14,616 --> 00:07:17,486
and it seems like
the skies are truly watching.

120
00:07:18,486 --> 00:07:21,756
The saying "spare the rod,
spoil the child" is true too.

121
00:07:23,396 --> 00:07:24,626
The reason I wanted to see you...

122
00:07:25,926 --> 00:07:27,996
My father-in-law agrees to this as well...

123
00:07:29,296 --> 00:07:33,366
How would you feel about
becoming part of our family?

124
00:07:34,136 --> 00:07:36,276
We'd make it official, legally.

125
00:07:37,476 --> 00:07:40,346
To put it plainly, we want to adopt you.

126
00:07:42,346 --> 00:07:44,746
That day you came to our house...

127
00:07:44,946 --> 00:07:47,286
left such a deep impression on me.

128
00:07:48,586 --> 00:07:51,756
I just couldn't stop thinking about...

129
00:07:51,986 --> 00:07:53,686
how well you turned out,
even without parents.

130
00:07:54,286 --> 00:07:58,096
If only Ye Jeong were
half as wonderful as you...

131
00:07:58,856 --> 00:08:02,326
I know you won't see us as parents yet,
or yourself as our daughter,

132
00:08:02,466 --> 00:08:04,136
but we'd grow on each other over time.

133
00:08:05,436 --> 00:08:08,066
We'll be your safety net.

134
00:08:08,636 --> 00:08:09,706
That's what we want to do for you.

135
00:08:10,776 --> 00:08:14,246
This isn't just out of a desire
to atone for Ye Jeong's awful behavior.

136
00:08:14,646 --> 00:08:16,516
We're not doing this just
to ease our own conscience.

137
00:08:17,276 --> 00:08:19,516
We've genuinely grown to care for you.

138
00:08:20,216 --> 00:08:22,286
I'm not as good a person
as you think...

139
00:08:23,286 --> 00:08:24,886
I have many shortcomings,

140
00:08:26,586 --> 00:08:28,226
and you might be disappointed.

141
00:08:28,226 --> 00:08:31,296
Could you be worse than Ye Jeong?

142
00:08:33,196 --> 00:08:37,096
I never imagined she was going around
acting like that.

143
00:08:38,966 --> 00:08:41,206
Now that she's cut us off and left,

144
00:08:43,206 --> 00:08:44,836
I'm trying my best not to think about her.

145
00:08:46,946 --> 00:08:49,106
I just hope that, wherever she is,
her spirit is repentant.

146
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:55,186
So what are you going to do?

147
00:08:57,116 --> 00:08:58,286
Should I even need to ask?

148
00:09:01,456 --> 00:09:03,096
This is what we always wished for.

149
00:09:06,226 --> 00:09:07,226
Well, good for you.

150
00:09:08,266 --> 00:09:11,336
You're getting sophisticated parents
from a loaded family.

151
00:09:12,496 --> 00:09:13,806
I'll still look out for you.

152
00:09:15,036 --> 00:09:16,036
How?

153
00:09:17,006 --> 00:09:18,776
By buying me a nice meal once in a while?

154
00:09:21,776 --> 00:09:25,876
They know you well, so I'm sure
they'll care about you too.

155
00:09:26,916 --> 00:09:29,286
They came to volunteer last week
and acted all friendly with me.

156
00:09:29,346 --> 00:09:31,616
They're planning to keep volunteering,
you know.

157
00:09:32,016 --> 00:09:34,156
And that's supposed to erase
all the pain we suffered?

158
00:09:34,926 --> 00:09:36,396
They're just doing it
to ease their own conscience.

159
00:09:36,956 --> 00:09:39,796
Either way, they're people to look up to,
aren't they?

160
00:09:39,866 --> 00:09:42,366
They should've just raised their kid right
in the first place.

161
00:09:42,626 --> 00:09:44,066
Was Tae Ye Jeong even human?

162
00:09:47,736 --> 00:09:48,736
So this is how...

163
00:09:50,976 --> 00:09:52,476
our friendship ends.

164
00:09:52,536 --> 00:09:53,646
Why would it end?

165
00:09:53,646 --> 00:09:56,316
It won't.
We'll just be living in different places.

166
00:09:56,446 --> 00:09:58,316
But that "different place" is
a completely different...

167
00:09:59,886 --> 00:10:02,486
You're becoming the legitimate daughter
of a lawyer at a top Seoul firm.

168
00:10:02,686 --> 00:10:04,816
You'll get to enjoy everything
that Tae Ye Jeong had,

169
00:10:06,656 --> 00:10:08,186
and our paths in life will diverge.

170
00:10:11,956 --> 00:10:12,996
I'm happy for you.

171
00:10:14,596 --> 00:10:15,596
Congratulations.

172
00:10:18,696 --> 00:10:19,706
Congratulations.

173
00:10:20,366 --> 00:10:21,706
This is such a surprise.

174
00:10:22,736 --> 00:10:25,606
It feels like a dream.
I really hope he's my dad.

175
00:10:35,046 --> 00:10:37,416
Are you Kim Young Jun, by any chance?

176
00:10:38,586 --> 00:10:39,586
Yes.

177
00:10:46,026 --> 00:10:47,026
Have you had dinner?

178
00:10:47,526 --> 00:10:49,426
We can get a simple meal here.

179
00:10:49,696 --> 00:10:50,696
Have you eaten?

180
00:10:51,266 --> 00:10:53,606
(Gimpo International Airport)

181
00:10:56,136 --> 00:10:57,506
What about the name Kim Jin Ju?

182
00:10:58,936 --> 00:11:01,806
It's just what I was named,
and what I've always been called.

183
00:11:02,306 --> 00:11:04,076
Was there a necklace with the baby's name,
by any chance?

184
00:11:07,016 --> 00:11:09,486
When I left her with a close friend
in Japan,

185
00:11:09,986 --> 00:11:10,986
I put it around her neck.

186
00:11:11,286 --> 00:11:14,356
I do have an earring.
A single pearl earring.

187
00:11:14,686 --> 00:11:17,496
- A pearl earring?
- They said it was in my baby blanket.

188
00:11:22,426 --> 00:11:24,296
So it's not me?

189
00:11:24,566 --> 00:11:26,136
No, I don't know.

190
00:11:27,366 --> 00:11:30,906
Someone could've swapped the gold necklace
for a pearl earring.

191
00:11:31,276 --> 00:11:34,746
It's a 14-karat gold post with a pearl.
It's not expensive.

192
00:11:34,876 --> 00:11:36,976
Did you ever hear anything
about coming from Japan?

193
00:11:38,246 --> 00:11:39,246
Me?

194
00:11:40,546 --> 00:11:41,546
No.

195
00:11:42,246 --> 00:11:44,786
Anything at all, no matter how small.

196
00:11:48,056 --> 00:11:51,596
There used to be a church
in Myeonghui-dong...

197
00:11:51,926 --> 00:11:55,626
affiliated with the Nua Children’s Home.
It was sold after the pastor passed away.

198
00:11:57,536 --> 00:12:00,536
I was apparently left in their baby box.

199
00:12:04,506 --> 00:12:07,146
I heard most of what I know
from that church.

200
00:12:08,076 --> 00:12:10,776
Some kids were left by parents
who couldn't afford to keep them,

201
00:12:11,416 --> 00:12:14,186
and others were there to escape
abuse from their parents.

202
00:12:15,316 --> 00:12:17,416
Was there anything else in your blanket,
like a note?

203
00:12:18,386 --> 00:12:19,756
Nothing besides the earring...

204
00:12:21,356 --> 00:12:22,356
Blood type?

205
00:12:23,396 --> 00:12:24,396
Type A.

206
00:12:24,896 --> 00:12:25,896
I'm Type A too.

207
00:12:28,466 --> 00:12:30,396
If I were the one left in Japan,

208
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:33,806
wouldn't I be in an institution
somewhere in Japan?

209
00:12:34,836 --> 00:12:36,936
After looking into it,
someone brought her...

210
00:12:37,276 --> 00:12:38,376
to Korea right away.

211
00:12:40,106 --> 00:12:42,606
We should get tested to be sure.

212
00:12:44,776 --> 00:12:45,776
Okay.

213
00:12:54,656 --> 00:12:56,126
Didn't you check my texts?

214
00:12:59,796 --> 00:13:01,666
The ceiling is leaking.

215
00:13:02,096 --> 00:13:04,836
I called management,
but they said the owner was abroad.

216
00:13:06,366 --> 00:13:08,206
If this is uncomfortable for you,
I'll go to a hotel.

217
00:13:11,876 --> 00:13:15,606
When you decided to become an actor,
how did your parents react?

218
00:13:15,746 --> 00:13:18,246
My father didn't speak to me for a month.

219
00:13:19,316 --> 00:13:20,586
We'll just have to wait and see.

220
00:13:35,726 --> 00:13:37,666
My car isn't being delivered
until next month.

221
00:13:38,196 --> 00:13:39,936
I can take the subway.

222
00:13:44,876 --> 00:13:46,846
See you Monday at ten, then.

223
00:13:47,676 --> 00:13:48,676
Okay.

224
00:13:54,686 --> 00:13:55,886
Drive safely, please.

225
00:13:56,186 --> 00:13:57,186
Will do.

226
00:14:15,436 --> 00:14:17,076
I'll be pretty busy through next week,

227
00:14:17,536 --> 00:14:19,806
so let's aim for the week after next.

228
00:14:20,046 --> 00:14:21,576
But if you'd just reconsider...

229
00:14:25,116 --> 00:14:26,146
Mind if I sit here?

230
00:14:30,956 --> 00:14:32,086
I was with a client too.

231
00:14:33,386 --> 00:14:34,426
I just saw them off.

232
00:14:35,056 --> 00:14:36,156
Was that an interview with Jin Yi Han?

233
00:14:36,456 --> 00:14:39,026
- Yes.
- Why were you so chummy in the interview?

234
00:14:40,426 --> 00:14:42,496
You barely made eye contact with me
during my interview.

235
00:14:43,066 --> 00:14:44,866
But you couldn't take your eyes off
Jin Yi Han.

236
00:14:45,336 --> 00:14:47,166
Am I supposed to look away
while he's answering my questions?

237
00:14:48,036 --> 00:14:49,306
Why the sudden formality?

238
00:14:49,706 --> 00:14:51,336
I suppose I'm just on edge.

239
00:14:51,876 --> 00:14:54,046
Are you on edge, or are you embarrassed?

240
00:14:55,776 --> 00:14:56,916
Because I saw right through you?

241
00:14:58,316 --> 00:14:59,986
This is just like the old you.

242
00:15:00,246 --> 00:15:02,686
- You're joking around again.
- I'm not joking.

243
00:15:03,156 --> 00:15:04,986
If I didn't know better,
I'd have thought he was your boyfriend.

244
00:15:07,956 --> 00:15:10,326
Let's do some serious drinking.
Tomorrow's the weekend.

245
00:15:13,796 --> 00:15:15,596
A bottle of 25-year Dickel, please.

246
00:15:15,896 --> 00:15:16,896
Right away, sir.

247
00:15:17,366 --> 00:15:19,066
Isn't that crazy expensive?

248
00:15:21,666 --> 00:15:22,666
Isn't that heavy?

249
00:15:23,036 --> 00:15:24,106
What if it is?

250
00:15:27,006 --> 00:15:28,046
You have a driver's license, right?

251
00:15:29,276 --> 00:15:31,416
I've decided on your birthday gift.
When's your birthday?

252
00:15:36,686 --> 00:15:39,016
You'll celebrate it at some point,
won't you?

253
00:15:40,126 --> 00:15:42,886
Since when are we close enough
for you to buy me a car?

254
00:15:43,756 --> 00:15:44,796
How could you say that?

255
00:15:45,596 --> 00:15:47,066
You're disappointing me
on so many levels today.

256
00:15:51,866 --> 00:15:53,266
Did you pick this place?

257
00:15:54,166 --> 00:15:56,436
- No.
- Don't you think he has a thing for you?

258
00:15:56,776 --> 00:15:58,606
Of course not. I'm just a reporter.

259
00:15:58,606 --> 00:16:00,376
You're a reporter, but also a woman.

260
00:16:01,446 --> 00:16:03,876
You really run hot and cold sometimes.

261
00:16:05,246 --> 00:16:07,016
That's a hurtful thing to say.

262
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:08,946
I'm not just talking about right now.

263
00:16:09,216 --> 00:16:12,316
Last time we were here,
you just ditched me and left.

264
00:16:13,156 --> 00:16:15,586
- I had an urgent assignment.
- Don't make excuses.

265
00:16:16,026 --> 00:16:17,296
I'm not that clueless.

266
00:16:17,626 --> 00:16:19,626
Back then...

267
00:16:22,296 --> 00:16:23,796
Put yourself in my shoes.

268
00:16:23,996 --> 00:16:25,066
Let's say I...

269
00:16:28,336 --> 00:16:30,506
(Ba Ra)

270
00:16:41,316 --> 00:16:42,886
The person you are calling is unavailable.

271
00:16:42,886 --> 00:16:45,886
Please leave a message after the tone.

272
00:16:53,826 --> 00:16:57,536
What if I only had eyes
for Director Shin Ju Shin?

273
00:16:58,036 --> 00:17:00,006
Since he's with Momo,

274
00:17:00,336 --> 00:17:02,306
wouldn't I seem pathetic to you?

275
00:17:03,906 --> 00:17:04,976
Pathetic?

276
00:17:06,306 --> 00:17:07,476
Now you get it.

277
00:17:07,546 --> 00:17:09,576
You're saying you thought
I was pathetic back then.

278
00:17:11,546 --> 00:17:12,576
It's different.

279
00:17:15,116 --> 00:17:16,186
I'll drink it straight.

280
00:17:29,966 --> 00:17:31,236
It is completely different.

281
00:17:31,236 --> 00:17:32,636
How much does it take you to get drunk?

282
00:17:32,966 --> 00:17:35,136
- I don't know.
- Meaning you can hold your liquor?

283
00:17:35,706 --> 00:17:37,136
Or you've just never drunk enough
to find out?

284
00:17:37,236 --> 00:17:39,436
You have to let your guard down
to get drunk,

285
00:17:39,806 --> 00:17:41,406
and I've pretty much never done that.

286
00:17:42,246 --> 00:17:44,116
I've even faked being drunk when I had to.

287
00:17:44,516 --> 00:17:46,146
I'm an expert at
secretly dumping my drinks.

288
00:17:46,546 --> 00:17:47,716
Don't do that tonight.

289
00:17:48,386 --> 00:17:49,486
This is too good to waste.

290
00:17:51,956 --> 00:17:52,956
Hey.

291
00:17:53,556 --> 00:17:54,556
Yes?

292
00:17:55,256 --> 00:17:56,456
I just felt like calling you.

293
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:05,466
You won't let your guard down,
even with me?

294
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:10,106
It's not like you're a stranger to me,

295
00:18:10,236 --> 00:18:12,006
and I'm not drinking because it's work.

296
00:18:15,546 --> 00:18:16,616
When...

297
00:18:17,446 --> 00:18:18,846
are you the happiest?

298
00:18:21,286 --> 00:18:22,316
I'm happy...

299
00:18:23,356 --> 00:18:25,786
- right now.
- Besides right now?

300
00:18:26,056 --> 00:18:28,286
- What about you?
- Me too. Right now.

301
00:18:28,726 --> 00:18:31,026
- It's nice.
- But I'm happy.

302
00:18:31,696 --> 00:18:33,096
It's just "nice" for you?

303
00:18:33,426 --> 00:18:36,066
Coming from me,
"nice" is the highest praise.

304
00:18:43,506 --> 00:18:44,576
Shin Ju Shin...

305
00:18:46,176 --> 00:18:47,606
is someone women would fall for.

306
00:18:48,846 --> 00:18:50,046
Do you like Director Shin too?

307
00:18:51,576 --> 00:18:52,576
Yes.

308
00:18:53,646 --> 00:18:55,316
He's got it all.

309
00:18:58,786 --> 00:19:02,386
His father passed away,
but he's the son of the esteemed Chairman.

310
00:19:03,456 --> 00:19:04,726
As the Chairman's son?

311
00:19:11,696 --> 00:19:12,696
How about...

312
00:19:13,666 --> 00:19:15,036
we trade houses?

313
00:19:16,006 --> 00:19:17,306
When I was at your place,

314
00:19:18,206 --> 00:19:19,736
it felt so comfortable and cozy.

315
00:19:20,806 --> 00:19:22,176
I feel like I'd sleep well there.

316
00:19:23,376 --> 00:19:26,516
It's not really my place.
Technically, it's An Hee's.

317
00:19:28,086 --> 00:19:29,086
Having trouble sleeping?

318
00:19:29,646 --> 00:19:30,916
I wouldn't call it insomnia.

319
00:19:31,656 --> 00:19:34,726
After living in such a big villa,
you'd feel cooped up.

320
00:19:36,086 --> 00:19:38,726
Besides, if you're alone,
it'll probably be the same everywhere.

321
00:19:49,736 --> 00:19:51,076
Slow down.

322
00:19:53,946 --> 00:19:55,476
Worried I'll get drunk and come on to you?

323
00:19:56,246 --> 00:19:57,376
I'm worried it'll be hard on you.

324
00:19:59,876 --> 00:20:02,946
A hangover is the least of my worries.

325
00:20:04,756 --> 00:20:08,386
Don't worry. I don't act out when drunk.
I've seen enough of it to be sick of it.

326
00:20:08,526 --> 00:20:11,126
I bet you making a scene
would be something to see.

327
00:20:11,556 --> 00:20:13,426
- To me, no matter what you do...
- Don't make me cuss at you.

328
00:20:13,496 --> 00:20:14,496
Go ahead.

329
00:20:15,066 --> 00:20:16,966
I'll even let you hit me today.

330
00:20:20,336 --> 00:20:22,736
- There's nothing I like here.
- What?

331
00:20:23,536 --> 00:20:24,636
Want me to order you spicy rice cakes?

332
00:20:25,436 --> 00:20:28,146
A long time ago,
I was standing outside a supermarket...

333
00:20:28,946 --> 00:20:29,976
Go on.

334
00:20:31,346 --> 00:20:33,276
I went there to eat snacks
to make myself feel better...

335
00:20:33,276 --> 00:20:35,146
after my teacher hurt me,

336
00:20:36,346 --> 00:20:37,616
but I couldn't buy anything.

337
00:20:42,526 --> 00:20:44,526
I saw all the other kids there
with their moms.

338
00:20:45,756 --> 00:20:47,526
And another was holding
their grandma's hand.

339
00:20:50,166 --> 00:20:54,306
In front of all those happy kids,
I felt so pathetic and small.

340
00:21:00,036 --> 00:21:01,276
We'll stop by a convenience store
on the way.

341
00:21:02,806 --> 00:21:06,416
You should either get a puppy
or find someone.

342
00:21:06,476 --> 00:21:08,016
There is no need to force
myself into a relationship.

343
00:21:08,016 --> 00:21:09,986
It'd help you relax and sleep better.

344
00:21:10,656 --> 00:21:13,256
If I can't sleep, I read or play games.

345
00:21:13,586 --> 00:21:16,226
- There's plenty to do.
- I'd love to get a puppy.

346
00:21:17,726 --> 00:21:18,796
You must be lonely.

347
00:21:19,496 --> 00:21:20,566
Want me to get you one?

348
00:21:20,796 --> 00:21:23,166
I can't just leave it alone all day.
That would be cruel.

349
00:21:25,496 --> 00:21:26,736
Why don't you move in with me?

350
00:21:28,506 --> 00:21:30,306
I'm not kidding. I've got spare rooms.

351
00:21:33,706 --> 00:21:34,746
Aren't you going to get married?

352
00:21:35,576 --> 00:21:37,246
You want people to think
we're living together?

353
00:21:37,476 --> 00:21:40,116
We would be.
We decided we'd live like family.

354
00:21:41,486 --> 00:21:42,486
So let's do it.

355
00:21:45,886 --> 00:21:47,156
Are you worried it'd ruin
my marriage chances?

356
00:21:47,426 --> 00:21:49,486
I'll just have to move out
again eventually.

357
00:21:50,156 --> 00:21:51,796
What woman would be okay with that?

358
00:21:52,196 --> 00:21:53,696
I'd basically be getting kicked out then.

359
00:21:55,226 --> 00:21:57,196
I don't want things to end
like that between us.

360
00:21:58,166 --> 00:22:01,566
Having a puppy is nice
for the companionship,

361
00:22:03,336 --> 00:22:06,306
but I want to be able to say "I love you."

362
00:22:08,776 --> 00:22:09,876
I've never been able to.

363
00:22:12,546 --> 00:22:13,586
Come to think of it, me neither.

364
00:22:16,116 --> 00:22:19,286
Not even to your parents?
Or to James?

365
00:22:19,586 --> 00:22:21,086
You really don't get guys, do you?

366
00:22:21,726 --> 00:22:22,786
To my own brother?

367
00:22:23,996 --> 00:22:25,726
There's so much I don't know.

368
00:22:26,056 --> 00:22:28,066
The hardest part for me
after my mom passed away...

369
00:22:30,866 --> 00:22:32,596
was never telling her I loved her.

370
00:22:34,206 --> 00:22:35,366
Not even once.

371
00:22:35,906 --> 00:22:36,906
Or rather, I didn't.

372
00:22:37,576 --> 00:22:39,576
I never thought she'd
pass away so suddenly.

373
00:22:40,846 --> 00:22:43,106
Then tell her now, in your heart.

374
00:22:43,646 --> 00:22:45,846
Like a prayer, every night
before you go to sleep.

375
00:22:46,446 --> 00:22:49,246
I'm sure she'll feel it.
The prayer from her loving son.

376
00:22:51,316 --> 00:22:52,356
You think she'll feel it?

377
00:22:53,016 --> 00:22:54,026
Yes.

378
00:22:54,726 --> 00:22:59,426
If it were me, I'd stay by my son's side
and protect him, even as a spirit.

379
00:23:15,546 --> 00:23:18,076
Let me pour you a drink.
You're not just anybody.

380
00:23:20,586 --> 00:23:21,716
Say that again...

381
00:23:23,416 --> 00:23:24,416
one more time.

382
00:23:29,086 --> 00:23:30,656
You're not just anybody.

383
00:23:31,356 --> 00:23:32,696
So we have something special, right?

384
00:23:36,366 --> 00:23:38,596
I'm definitely getting drunk tonight.

385
00:23:48,746 --> 00:23:51,316
You want to say "I love you" to a puppy?

386
00:23:51,476 --> 00:23:54,816
Yes. Someone to love and care for.

387
00:23:55,646 --> 00:23:57,456
I wish I had someone like that in my life.

388
00:23:58,616 --> 00:23:59,916
Wouldn't I be a better choice...

389
00:24:00,886 --> 00:24:02,286
than a dog?

390
00:24:08,796 --> 00:24:09,796
I love you.

391
00:24:14,436 --> 00:24:15,466
I didn't mean it.

392
00:24:19,006 --> 00:24:22,746
A dog only has eyes for its owner,
and they never waver.

393
00:24:23,876 --> 00:24:25,716
They're animals that deserve to be loved.

394
00:24:28,816 --> 00:24:29,946
What am I to you?

395
00:24:30,916 --> 00:24:33,516
I'm very clear on what you are to me.

396
00:24:36,156 --> 00:24:37,296
Clear in what way?

397
00:24:39,596 --> 00:24:41,926
That I'm definitely like a little sister,
six years younger?

398
00:24:42,926 --> 00:24:43,936
Something that will never change.

399
00:24:45,466 --> 00:24:47,006
So you don't want to be
a distant benefactor,

400
00:24:47,466 --> 00:24:49,466
but someone closer to me?

401
00:24:53,006 --> 00:24:54,006
That's right.

402
00:24:55,106 --> 00:24:58,076
Anyway, a true bond is
something that doesn't change.

403
00:24:58,376 --> 00:24:59,646
Just like the bond
between a parent and child.

404
00:25:01,886 --> 00:25:03,086
What, are we family now?

405
00:25:08,886 --> 00:25:11,796
In TV shows, when a mom says to her kids,

406
00:25:11,996 --> 00:25:13,256
or a daughter to her mom,

407
00:25:14,366 --> 00:25:16,266
"I love you,"

408
00:25:18,236 --> 00:25:20,806
I've always wondered what that felt like.

409
00:25:24,176 --> 00:25:25,176
I love you.

410
00:25:28,806 --> 00:25:30,546
I'll always love you,

411
00:25:30,816 --> 00:25:31,816
my sweet girl.

412
00:25:36,246 --> 00:25:38,016
Today's the day we confessed
our love to each other.

413
00:25:38,986 --> 00:25:39,986
Remember this.

414
00:25:45,426 --> 00:25:46,426
Long time no see.

415
00:25:47,666 --> 00:25:48,666
My gosh.

416
00:25:50,266 --> 00:25:51,496
He's someone I'm interviewing.

417
00:25:52,436 --> 00:25:54,166
He was a senior in my college club.

418
00:25:55,006 --> 00:25:58,006
- And your name, sir?
- Ha Yong Joong.

419
00:25:58,076 --> 00:25:59,136
I'm Yoo Seon Oh.

420
00:26:00,606 --> 00:26:02,246
We just finished round one,
and this is round two for us.

421
00:26:03,376 --> 00:26:05,246
We haven't met, have we?

422
00:26:06,776 --> 00:26:08,446
Your friends are waiting for you.

423
00:26:08,516 --> 00:26:09,686
Keep in touch.

424
00:26:10,016 --> 00:26:12,656
We're in the same business,
but I never see you.

425
00:26:12,916 --> 00:26:13,926
Sure.

426
00:26:14,356 --> 00:26:15,356
Then.

427
00:26:17,726 --> 00:26:18,996
Wait a second.

428
00:26:18,996 --> 00:26:21,426
Are you that...

429
00:26:21,796 --> 00:26:22,826
WorldNet?

430
00:26:23,596 --> 00:26:25,496
- Yes.
- It's an honor.

431
00:26:27,836 --> 00:26:28,836
(Taewon Daily, Yoo Seon Oh)

432
00:26:29,036 --> 00:26:30,166
I don't have a business card on me...

433
00:26:30,706 --> 00:26:34,476
- How about a picture instead...
- He's being interviewed.

434
00:26:35,676 --> 00:26:39,416
I'm a huge fan of Lost Knights.
You owe me a meal.

435
00:26:39,846 --> 00:26:41,316
- Yes, anytime...
- You promise?

436
00:26:41,916 --> 00:26:43,246
- Okay.
- She's our witness.

437
00:26:45,586 --> 00:26:46,956
- Until then.
- Right.

438
00:26:55,566 --> 00:26:56,896
Let's have a proper drink next time.

439
00:27:01,136 --> 00:27:03,706
- Keep the bottle for us. Check, please.
- Yes, sir.

440
00:27:04,276 --> 00:27:06,676
- Should we go see Ju Shin?
- You should go.

441
00:27:06,736 --> 00:27:08,806
- Together.
- Why would I go?

442
00:27:08,876 --> 00:27:11,976
Ju Shin needs to accept you
as my little sister now.

443
00:27:12,646 --> 00:27:14,516
Would you like that if you were him?

444
00:27:15,246 --> 00:27:16,246
Why wouldn't he?

445
00:27:16,516 --> 00:27:18,516
He said he doesn't tolerate people
crossing boundaries.

446
00:27:18,716 --> 00:27:20,956
Ju Shin said that to you?

447
00:27:22,056 --> 00:27:23,856
He summoned me once.

448
00:27:27,796 --> 00:27:28,796
Get in.

449
00:27:30,566 --> 00:27:31,566
Get in.

450
00:27:35,006 --> 00:27:37,336
You should call him first.
He might be asleep.

451
00:27:37,736 --> 00:27:41,576
With us, showing up unannounced
gets you an even bigger welcome.

452
00:27:41,846 --> 00:27:43,406
We need to establish your place with us.

453
00:27:43,746 --> 00:27:46,346
That may be true for you, but it's rude.

454
00:27:46,476 --> 00:27:47,746
Trust me on this.

455
00:27:49,986 --> 00:27:51,156
Then at least text him.

456
00:28:25,616 --> 00:28:28,256
Careful. It's slippery, you'll get hurt.

457
00:28:34,966 --> 00:28:37,336
I don't feel like it. You go in alone.

458
00:29:10,996 --> 00:29:12,166
Director Shin.

459
00:29:12,436 --> 00:29:15,536
Since you're getting married,
you'll be getting a lot of press.

460
00:29:16,106 --> 00:29:19,276
I got a suit that would look great on you.
I got it at cost.

461
00:29:20,006 --> 00:29:22,446
I've only seen you in a suit a few times,

462
00:29:22,976 --> 00:29:24,916
but with my professional eye,

463
00:29:24,976 --> 00:29:26,476
I thought there was some room
for improvement.

464
00:29:26,746 --> 00:29:27,746
Jin Ju.

465
00:29:28,246 --> 00:29:31,616
- Hurry up. I have to get to a wedding.
- Yes, sir.

466
00:29:34,826 --> 00:29:38,156
What should I wear?
The press is going to swarm the place.

467
00:29:40,026 --> 00:29:42,696
My boss sent me to give you this.

468
00:29:43,026 --> 00:29:44,866
Take it back. I can't accept this.

469
00:29:44,936 --> 00:29:47,306
My boss is just a very generous person.

470
00:29:47,306 --> 00:29:48,366
This is way too much.

471
00:29:48,936 --> 00:29:52,006
They say even fish can't live
in water that's too pure.

472
00:29:53,876 --> 00:29:55,006
Are you trying...

473
00:29:55,946 --> 00:29:57,046
to lecture me?

474
00:30:05,656 --> 00:30:08,426
I got the suit.
We should grab a meal sometime.

475
00:30:11,196 --> 00:30:14,396
(We're ready for surgery.)

476
00:30:19,336 --> 00:30:22,006
Did your interview run late yesterday?

477
00:30:24,136 --> 00:30:25,336
Are you sure he's your dad?

478
00:30:25,806 --> 00:30:26,906
I hope so.

479
00:30:27,036 --> 00:30:30,046
He's so young.
He said he was 20 when I was born.

480
00:30:30,446 --> 00:30:32,446
We're scheduled for a DNA test on Monday.

481
00:30:32,646 --> 00:30:36,216
- What's he like?
- I bet he was a real looker in his day.

482
00:30:37,016 --> 00:30:39,116
- He's single.
- Sure he's not a con artist?

483
00:30:39,116 --> 00:30:40,156
Nowadays, it's gotten more sophisticated.

484
00:30:40,216 --> 00:30:43,426
What could he possibly con me out of?
It's not like I have anything.

485
00:30:44,656 --> 00:30:46,196
We'll do the test, and if it's negative,

486
00:30:46,196 --> 00:30:48,766
I'll just say goodbye,
and that will be it.

487
00:30:49,566 --> 00:30:50,566
But...

488
00:30:51,036 --> 00:30:52,366
My heart just...

489
00:30:55,066 --> 00:30:56,866
Shoot. I have to go.

490
00:30:57,266 --> 00:30:58,536
If your boss is calling, then this...

491
00:30:58,606 --> 00:31:00,746
No, it's my manager.
He's got a short fuse...

492
00:31:02,546 --> 00:31:03,676
I'll see you later.

493
00:31:18,556 --> 00:31:20,766
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

494
00:31:30,836 --> 00:31:32,776
(Kim Jin Ju)

495
00:31:34,206 --> 00:31:35,206
(I got the suit...)

496
00:31:40,016 --> 00:31:43,246
Thank you for the suit.
Are you free for dinner tonight?

497
00:31:53,656 --> 00:31:56,296
Thank you for the suit.
Can you do dinner tonight?

498
00:31:59,096 --> 00:32:00,196
Yes, Director Shin.

499
00:32:37,776 --> 00:32:39,736
- Kim Jin Ju?
- Yes.

500
00:32:53,456 --> 00:32:54,486
Did you have lunch?

501
00:32:55,186 --> 00:32:57,556
I just had some snacks
at my friend's place.

502
00:32:57,896 --> 00:32:58,896
You must be hungry, then.

503
00:32:59,156 --> 00:33:00,356
What about you, Director Shin?

504
00:33:00,966 --> 00:33:01,966
You're friends...

505
00:33:03,366 --> 00:33:04,366
with Geum Ba Ra?

506
00:33:06,166 --> 00:33:07,166
Yes.

507
00:33:08,306 --> 00:33:09,836
Are both of you still single?

508
00:33:10,766 --> 00:33:11,776
A boyfriend.

509
00:33:14,006 --> 00:33:15,006
Right.

510
00:33:16,006 --> 00:33:17,146
So what do you do for fun?

511
00:33:19,016 --> 00:33:20,376
I enjoy my work.

512
00:33:26,916 --> 00:33:27,956
Ladies first.

513
00:33:44,066 --> 00:33:45,506
They're Baccarat glasses.

514
00:33:46,806 --> 00:33:48,506
Since you just moved here from abroad,

515
00:33:48,776 --> 00:33:50,776
I figured you might not have anything.

516
00:33:51,676 --> 00:33:53,316
And these are things you'll need.

517
00:33:54,616 --> 00:33:57,716
Clients, gallery owners, and reporters...

518
00:33:58,316 --> 00:34:00,786
will all be dropping by your studio
frequently now.

519
00:34:04,996 --> 00:34:07,296
Have you tried this?

520
00:34:11,236 --> 00:34:12,236
Mr. Kim.

521
00:34:15,566 --> 00:34:16,906
Aren't you lonely?

522
00:34:17,606 --> 00:34:20,306
Isn't everyone a little lonely?

523
00:34:20,876 --> 00:34:22,406
The character for "person..."

524
00:34:24,146 --> 00:34:25,876
shows two people...

525
00:34:26,676 --> 00:34:28,046
leaning on each other.

526
00:34:30,846 --> 00:34:34,016
It's only natural for us
to rely on each other to get by.

527
00:34:35,256 --> 00:34:37,126
That's what my mother used to say.

528
00:34:40,966 --> 00:34:41,966
I...

529
00:34:42,866 --> 00:34:44,766
at least have my beautiful daughter.

530
00:34:45,936 --> 00:34:47,096
Are you offering...

531
00:34:47,866 --> 00:34:49,036
to be my friend?

532
00:34:52,576 --> 00:34:53,776
Just...

533
00:34:54,476 --> 00:34:55,476
a friend?

534
00:34:57,306 --> 00:34:58,716
Someone I can confide in.

535
00:35:05,256 --> 00:35:06,256
How about me?

536
00:35:08,256 --> 00:35:10,756
Have you tried this?

537
00:35:11,826 --> 00:35:13,426
This wine is on a whole other level.

538
00:35:13,556 --> 00:35:15,126
It's from my private collection.

539
00:35:20,436 --> 00:35:24,006
You know, you really play favorites.

540
00:35:24,736 --> 00:35:26,976
- To CEO Ju Yeong Ae...
- Hyun Ran Hee.

541
00:35:29,846 --> 00:35:30,946
What do you think you're doing?

542
00:35:31,776 --> 00:35:33,616
- Mr. Kim.
- I'm...

543
00:35:34,116 --> 00:35:35,116
Kim Young Jun.

544
00:35:38,256 --> 00:35:39,486
Did you forget my name too?

545
00:35:40,956 --> 00:35:42,026
I...

546
00:35:42,956 --> 00:35:43,956
Are you...

547
00:35:49,796 --> 00:35:51,736
No way. Absolutely not.

548
00:35:51,966 --> 00:35:53,666
I was in a car accident in Germany.

549
00:35:53,996 --> 00:35:55,006
A bad one.

550
00:35:58,206 --> 00:36:00,176
- You completely forgot all about me.
- Did you...

551
00:36:00,536 --> 00:36:01,846
get a whole new face?

552
00:36:01,846 --> 00:36:03,146
Let's just say you forgot about me.

553
00:36:05,216 --> 00:36:06,846
But did you also completely forget
about the child you abandoned?

554
00:36:07,516 --> 00:36:09,416
How can you live so carefree
with a clear conscience?

555
00:36:09,886 --> 00:36:12,356
- Who says I abandoned her? She had a dad.
- I don't want to speak with you.

556
00:36:14,786 --> 00:36:16,356
And I hope I never see you again.

557
00:36:16,556 --> 00:36:17,926
Wasn't his name Pyeon Seung Jae?

558
00:36:18,596 --> 00:36:20,326
The one whose father was a doctor.

559
00:36:20,326 --> 00:36:22,366
I heard from him that you went to Japan.

560
00:36:28,266 --> 00:36:29,266
What about our child?

561
00:36:33,036 --> 00:36:34,136
In Germany?

562
00:36:34,506 --> 00:36:37,006
The daughter of the woman
who worked for our family for ages...

563
00:36:37,946 --> 00:36:40,516
moved to Japan, did very well,
and opened a big restaurant.

564
00:36:40,776 --> 00:36:42,316
She was born at our house.

565
00:36:43,246 --> 00:36:44,246
I think I remember hearing that.

566
00:36:44,316 --> 00:36:47,616
I gave her the baby and went to Germany,
but had an accident upon arrival.

567
00:36:47,686 --> 00:36:51,156
My recovery took a long time,
but I was determined to make it through.

568
00:36:51,896 --> 00:36:55,326
After ten years, I tried to contact her,
but I couldn't get to her.

569
00:36:56,296 --> 00:36:59,696
I was worried, but I trusted her
to raise our daughter well.

570
00:36:59,866 --> 00:37:02,136
After everything our family did for her.

571
00:37:03,536 --> 00:37:06,876
A few years ago, I went to look for them,
but her restaurant was gone.

572
00:37:06,936 --> 00:37:08,976
So I asked around
at the neighboring shops.

573
00:37:10,106 --> 00:37:12,316
They told me she had died
just days after I left.

574
00:37:12,616 --> 00:37:14,946
- Why?
- It was her Yakuza boyfriend.

575
00:37:16,286 --> 00:37:18,116
It was a crime of passion, apparently.

576
00:37:20,286 --> 00:37:21,286
And our daughter?

577
00:37:24,956 --> 00:37:26,196
Did something happen to her?

578
00:37:26,926 --> 00:37:29,696
All I could find out was
that she was brought back to Korea.

579
00:37:29,766 --> 00:37:31,266
When? Who brought her back?

580
00:37:31,466 --> 00:37:34,036
There was a Korean lady at the eatery.

581
00:37:34,606 --> 00:37:35,736
She brought her back...

582
00:37:36,036 --> 00:37:37,306
What was her name?

583
00:37:37,706 --> 00:37:39,006
How would I know?

584
00:37:39,106 --> 00:37:40,636
I was only there one night.

585
00:37:40,736 --> 00:37:42,946
All I remember is she had a round face.

586
00:37:44,416 --> 00:37:46,046
There were no records of her?

587
00:37:51,386 --> 00:37:52,616
I had no idea.

588
00:37:55,386 --> 00:37:56,386
I just thought she was in Japan,

589
00:37:57,796 --> 00:37:59,256
living a good life.

590
00:38:03,696 --> 00:38:05,396
So, is that woman raising her, then?

591
00:38:05,766 --> 00:38:07,066
I went to the police,

592
00:38:07,696 --> 00:38:11,676
but there was nothing they could do.
So, grasping at straws, I hired a PI.

593
00:38:15,106 --> 00:38:16,476
He said he couldn't make any promises.

594
00:38:20,716 --> 00:38:23,116
If she's alive, right now she'd be...

595
00:38:26,356 --> 00:38:27,716
You never even registered her birth?

596
00:38:29,456 --> 00:38:30,656
Are you blaming me now?

597
00:38:31,456 --> 00:38:32,496
You just dumped her on me...

598
00:38:32,496 --> 00:38:34,596
when my family was falling apart,
and then disappeared.

599
00:38:36,166 --> 00:38:39,536
She'd always adored me,
so I assumed she'd raise her well.

600
00:38:42,836 --> 00:38:44,336
I had a necklace made
with her name and put it on her.

601
00:38:46,276 --> 00:38:48,776
What name did you use?

602
00:38:48,976 --> 00:38:50,346
Her paternal grandmother's.

603
00:38:51,146 --> 00:38:53,376
The characters for Jin and Ju.

604
00:38:55,586 --> 00:38:58,616
Kim Jin Ju?

605
00:39:05,756 --> 00:39:08,766
Don't tell me it's that Kim Jin Ju.

606
00:39:09,066 --> 00:39:10,066
Hello?

607
00:39:10,826 --> 00:39:11,836
No, it can't be.

608
00:39:12,696 --> 00:39:13,696
Hello.

609
00:39:15,006 --> 00:39:17,566
Yes, I'll check with the gallery.

610
00:39:20,876 --> 00:39:22,446
There's a wrapped painting in my room.

611
00:39:22,446 --> 00:39:23,806
It's next to my desk. Go get it.

612
00:39:23,976 --> 00:39:24,976
Okay.

613
00:39:28,146 --> 00:39:29,286
Is she new?

614
00:39:29,986 --> 00:39:31,486
Momo's new stylist. She started last week.

615
00:39:31,756 --> 00:39:34,286
- Is she trustworthy?
- Yes.

616
00:39:36,156 --> 00:39:38,626
- Momo's new stylist.
- Kim Jin Ju?

617
00:39:39,126 --> 00:39:40,356
Did you run a background check on her?

618
00:39:40,626 --> 00:39:41,626
No.

619
00:39:41,766 --> 00:39:42,826
You need to.

620
00:39:43,226 --> 00:39:46,596
You can't be too careful these days.
She could leak information.

621
00:39:47,936 --> 00:39:50,606
- Is she discreet?
- She's quiet and seems composed.

622
00:39:51,206 --> 00:39:53,136
You know how many people
talk behind your back.

623
00:39:53,476 --> 00:39:54,576
You can't judge a book by its cover.

624
00:39:55,706 --> 00:39:57,946
That sponsored bracelet
that went missing last year...

625
00:39:58,546 --> 00:40:00,116
I'm sure that was an inside job.

626
00:40:01,646 --> 00:40:02,646
What do her parents do?

627
00:40:03,416 --> 00:40:04,486
I don't know that...

628
00:40:17,996 --> 00:40:18,996
It's good, isn't it?

629
00:40:20,336 --> 00:40:21,336
Yes.

630
00:40:21,966 --> 00:40:23,406
Is James treating you well?

631
00:40:23,666 --> 00:40:26,236
- Yes.
- Where did you work before this?

632
00:40:26,736 --> 00:40:29,206
I worked under Park Min Ja.

633
00:40:31,776 --> 00:40:34,146
You don't need to use honorifics
for her when you speak to me.

634
00:40:34,846 --> 00:40:36,486
Does Park Min Ja outrank me?

635
00:40:37,986 --> 00:40:38,986
Yes.

636
00:40:39,886 --> 00:40:42,286
Order a Coke.
Everyone has Coke with pizza, right?

637
00:40:42,756 --> 00:40:44,456
I don't really drink soda.

638
00:40:45,456 --> 00:40:48,526
Good. If you're next to Momo,
constantly sipping on things like that,

639
00:40:48,596 --> 00:40:50,196
how difficult do you think
that makes it for her?

640
00:40:50,696 --> 00:40:52,266
She's dieting like her life depends on it,

641
00:40:52,796 --> 00:40:54,096
even when she has such a big appetite.

642
00:40:56,966 --> 00:40:58,176
So, what do your parents do?

643
00:41:02,306 --> 00:41:03,506
Are they divorced?

644
00:41:07,146 --> 00:41:10,516
I grew up in an orphanage.

645
00:41:25,566 --> 00:41:28,706
Don't worry, CEO Hyun.
I hired her because she's a hard worker,

646
00:41:29,066 --> 00:41:31,006
and you know I'm a better judge
of character than anyone.

647
00:41:31,676 --> 00:41:33,206
I wouldn't pair Momo with just anyone.

648
00:41:38,546 --> 00:41:39,816
We'll have to wait and see.

649
00:41:39,816 --> 00:41:41,686
How she's always walking on eggshells...

650
00:41:41,746 --> 00:41:43,016
She's better than some clumsy fool.

651
00:41:43,086 --> 00:41:44,956
I fear she's a wolf in sheep's clothing.

652
00:41:45,816 --> 00:41:47,856
Mom, you can be a little too
suspicious of people.

653
00:41:55,666 --> 00:41:56,826
(Momo)

654
00:41:56,896 --> 00:41:59,236
Tell Jin Ju to come up before she leaves.

655
00:42:10,746 --> 00:42:12,446
You'll get an upset stomach. Slow down.

656
00:42:13,176 --> 00:42:14,376
Have some milk with it.

657
00:42:17,446 --> 00:42:18,956
Mom, did you just get here?

658
00:42:19,886 --> 00:42:20,886
No.

659
00:42:21,316 --> 00:42:23,826
Then did you make these yourself?

660
00:42:25,156 --> 00:42:26,996
It's not like making a sandwich
takes that long.

661
00:42:28,466 --> 00:42:31,366
Jin Ju, your hair is so lovely and thick.

662
00:42:32,696 --> 00:42:33,796
Let me compare.

663
00:42:39,276 --> 00:42:42,076
My hair just keeps getting
thinner with age...

664
00:42:45,676 --> 00:42:46,676
Mom.

665
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:49,386
Look at how thick it is.

666
00:43:02,666 --> 00:43:03,796
Why are you so tense?

667
00:43:04,366 --> 00:43:05,396
You're making me uncomfortable.

668
00:43:10,906 --> 00:43:11,906
Nice earrings.

669
00:43:12,876 --> 00:43:15,046
- Drink up.
- I'll take my time.

670
00:43:19,116 --> 00:43:20,116
Are you a lightweight?

671
00:43:20,646 --> 00:43:21,686
I can't drink much...

672
00:43:22,216 --> 00:43:23,746
My driver will take you home.

673
00:43:26,116 --> 00:43:28,486
I couldn't possibly take your ride, sir.

674
00:43:29,056 --> 00:43:30,056
I live nearby.

675
00:43:30,656 --> 00:43:31,696
I'm going to walk to sober up anyway.

676
00:43:34,296 --> 00:43:35,296
Were they a gift?

677
00:43:37,626 --> 00:43:39,566
They said they were in my baby blanket.

678
00:43:41,866 --> 00:43:43,106
Do you resent your parents?

679
00:43:44,806 --> 00:43:46,936
I'm sure they had their reasons.

680
00:43:48,476 --> 00:43:49,776
That's a wise way to think about it.

681
00:43:51,946 --> 00:43:53,846
Did Momo ever give you
a hard time at work?

682
00:43:54,616 --> 00:43:55,646
Not at all.

683
00:43:55,986 --> 00:43:57,616
She was a total nightmare.

684
00:43:58,556 --> 00:43:59,716
Are you managing to save any money?

685
00:44:00,956 --> 00:44:02,626
- I am.
- What for?

686
00:44:03,586 --> 00:44:04,586
To get your own place?

687
00:44:04,926 --> 00:44:07,496
First, I want to take a trip.

688
00:44:07,696 --> 00:44:08,766
Where to?

689
00:44:09,596 --> 00:44:12,636
- Japan.
- For the food? Shopping?

690
00:44:12,696 --> 00:44:13,696
Both.

691
00:44:15,706 --> 00:44:16,706
Lots of expenses will come up.

692
00:44:23,176 --> 00:44:24,846
(DNA Analysis Report)

693
00:44:28,616 --> 00:44:29,616
(DNA Analysis Report)

694
00:44:29,686 --> 00:44:32,016
(DNA Test Report)

695
00:44:41,866 --> 00:44:42,866
Here.

696
00:44:45,936 --> 00:44:46,936
It's a gift certificate.

697
00:44:47,336 --> 00:44:48,936
- No, I couldn't.
- I had it lying around.

698
00:44:49,406 --> 00:44:50,506
I don't need it.

699
00:44:52,036 --> 00:44:54,106
Go on, take it. It was a gift.

700
00:44:56,606 --> 00:44:58,716
But you already treated me
to such a nice dinner.

701
00:45:01,716 --> 00:45:02,986
Thank you.

702
00:45:06,986 --> 00:45:08,016
So is the job a good fit for you?

703
00:45:09,126 --> 00:45:10,126
Yes.

704
00:45:10,586 --> 00:45:12,356
(DNA Test Report)

705
00:45:18,596 --> 00:45:21,096
(Subjects: Kim Young Jun, Kim Jin Ju)

706
00:45:21,466 --> 00:45:26,176
(Paternity Probability: Non-match)

707
00:45:36,916 --> 00:45:38,986
I have plenty of great paintings,
you know.

708
00:45:39,156 --> 00:45:41,416
I mean, we're not talking
about a couple of grand here.

709
00:45:41,656 --> 00:45:43,756
Then just consider it a loan.

710
00:45:43,956 --> 00:45:45,356
Keep it on your wall for a few years.

711
00:45:45,726 --> 00:45:47,526
- Mr. Ha.
- Yes?

712
00:45:47,726 --> 00:45:49,696
Would you rather take this back
and continue...

713
00:45:49,696 --> 00:45:51,126
your relationship with Yong Joong and me?

714
00:45:51,296 --> 00:45:54,696
Or should I take this piece
and we call it quits today?

715
00:45:56,106 --> 00:45:57,906
Give it here. I'll take it back.

716
00:45:58,676 --> 00:46:00,876
Manager Yoon, take this back to my office.

717
00:46:02,506 --> 00:46:05,546
Goodness, I'm no match for you,
Reporter Geum.

718
00:46:06,076 --> 00:46:08,216
It's okay to let your junior win
every once in a while.

719
00:46:08,286 --> 00:46:09,946
What do you mean, junior?

720
00:46:10,216 --> 00:46:11,916
Even your rejections are clever.

721
00:46:12,186 --> 00:46:14,256
- Some drinks, please.
- Yes, sir.

722
00:46:14,556 --> 00:46:16,626
Don't you feel peckish?
Shall we order something?

723
00:46:16,626 --> 00:46:17,756
It's the perfect time for a snack.

724
00:46:17,826 --> 00:46:20,126
What are you in the mood for? My treat.

725
00:46:20,196 --> 00:46:22,896
Especially after the huge spread
you gave me last time.

726
00:46:23,096 --> 00:46:25,236
- My pleasure.
- Me too.

727
00:46:26,436 --> 00:46:27,566
How about some jokbal?

728
00:46:28,306 --> 00:46:30,206
On second thought,
that's not really fitting for you.

729
00:46:30,466 --> 00:46:33,576
- I'm willing to try it.
- Wait, you've never had jokbal?

730
00:46:34,836 --> 00:46:35,846
No.

731
00:46:37,146 --> 00:46:38,816
Let's go with lamb and hummus instead.

732
00:46:39,546 --> 00:46:42,016
- But you can't get that delivered.
- I'm James.

733
00:46:46,756 --> 00:46:48,956
Is Jin Ju out on assignment?

734
00:47:04,566 --> 00:47:09,206
I should've told you

735
00:47:11,676 --> 00:47:17,786
That I loved you

736
00:47:19,556 --> 00:47:24,256
That without you

737
00:47:26,226 --> 00:47:32,036
I can't live on

738
00:47:34,166 --> 00:47:39,306
That I love you

739
00:47:40,836 --> 00:47:45,916
I should have said it

740
00:47:48,686 --> 00:47:55,686
But I hesitated

741
00:47:55,926 --> 00:48:01,826
And my love is gone

742
00:48:04,326 --> 00:48:06,636
I gave you my heart

743
00:48:11,666 --> 00:48:14,236
I gave you my tears

744
00:48:18,816 --> 00:48:21,376
And I gave you my dreams

745
00:48:25,516 --> 00:48:30,926
But you drifted away

746
00:48:31,896 --> 00:48:37,626
My love is far away

747
00:48:45,476 --> 00:48:47,606
What do I have to do, go pray at a temple?

748
00:48:49,076 --> 00:48:51,146
I just can't give her up. I can't.

749
00:49:13,496 --> 00:49:15,106
Everything...

750
00:49:21,636 --> 00:49:24,376
All of it...

751
00:49:27,116 --> 00:49:28,416
(Geum Ba Ra)

752
00:49:38,156 --> 00:49:39,296
Hey, Ba Ra.

753
00:49:40,596 --> 00:49:41,626
Have you been drinking?

754
00:49:42,996 --> 00:49:43,996
A little.

755
00:49:45,866 --> 00:49:48,566
Are the results not a match?

756
00:49:52,376 --> 00:49:53,576
Not a match.

757
00:49:57,146 --> 00:49:58,406
With my luck, who was I kidding?

758
00:49:59,976 --> 00:50:02,386
I really had my hopes up all weekend.

759
00:50:03,186 --> 00:50:04,686
And I was so happy.

760
00:50:05,386 --> 00:50:08,286
- Go to bed.
- You pathetic fool.

761
00:50:11,486 --> 00:50:13,796
Pathetic or not,

762
00:50:14,556 --> 00:50:15,596
I'm still...

763
00:50:16,126 --> 00:50:18,126
your biggest fan.

764
00:50:25,376 --> 00:50:26,836
That venomous witch.

765
00:50:58,036 --> 00:51:00,706
Careful. It's slippery, you'll get hurt.

766
00:51:01,236 --> 00:51:04,076
Where does it hurt? Is it your spine?
Your tailbone?

767
00:51:05,476 --> 00:51:06,516
I don't know.

768
00:51:08,886 --> 00:51:10,016
Ju Shin's here.

769
00:51:17,086 --> 00:51:18,826
Sorry.

770
00:51:31,336 --> 00:51:32,576
Are you shocked?

771
00:51:34,706 --> 00:51:35,776
Shocked about what?

772
00:51:45,386 --> 00:51:46,456
I'm going.

773
00:51:59,866 --> 00:52:05,376
(Available)

774
00:52:06,736 --> 00:52:09,706
- Myeonghui-dong, please.
- You should get off first. It's closer.

775
00:52:10,206 --> 00:52:11,206
Myeonghui-dong, please.

776
00:52:19,186 --> 00:52:20,686
See? Just listen to me from now on.

777
00:52:30,466 --> 00:52:31,726
Is there a convenience store nearby?

778
00:52:31,866 --> 00:52:32,936
They're everywhere.

779
00:52:35,096 --> 00:52:36,106
Don't worry about it.

780
00:52:37,106 --> 00:52:39,036
Sir, the Itanic Palace, please.

781
00:52:39,336 --> 00:52:40,876
No, Myeonghui-dong, please.

782
00:52:50,586 --> 00:52:51,586
Right here, please.

783
00:52:56,526 --> 00:52:57,526
What looks good?

784
00:53:15,906 --> 00:53:18,206
- I'll get fat if I eat this at night.
- You need to gain some.

785
00:53:21,216 --> 00:53:22,446
If you get fired for gaining weight,

786
00:53:23,116 --> 00:53:24,116
you've got me to lean on.

787
00:53:25,186 --> 00:53:26,386
Then I'll get ice cream, too.

788
00:53:31,686 --> 00:53:33,196
It's the first day
since we confessed our love,

789
00:53:33,656 --> 00:53:34,726
but this is a pretty weak celebration.

790
00:53:35,896 --> 00:53:36,896
It's plenty.

791
00:53:37,866 --> 00:53:38,996
So I'm your number one, right?

792
00:53:41,936 --> 00:53:43,236
I'm happy being third.

793
00:53:44,436 --> 00:53:47,106
James, Momo, and then me.

794
00:53:48,436 --> 00:53:49,446
Whatever.

795
00:53:51,246 --> 00:53:52,316
There's a taxi.

796
00:53:55,316 --> 00:53:56,316
Go on.

797
00:54:29,586 --> 00:54:30,686
Sweet dreams.

798
00:55:24,266 --> 00:55:27,476
Isn't that the story? The broke girl
who's all alone snags the prince?

799
00:55:29,646 --> 00:55:31,206
Your bones look fine.

800
00:55:32,216 --> 00:55:33,716
Is it a sprained ligament then?

801
00:55:34,746 --> 00:55:35,946
Should I get some physical therapy?

802
00:55:37,016 --> 00:55:40,116
We need to know how much production costs,
like talent fees, have spiked.

803
00:55:40,186 --> 00:55:43,926
We need concrete figures,
not just what the PR people are saying.

804
00:55:43,986 --> 00:55:45,026
Get some solid quotes...

805
00:55:45,026 --> 00:55:46,826
from production company CEOs
or top executives.

806
00:55:47,156 --> 00:55:49,296
- Understood.
- Kwon Woo Seok.

807
00:55:49,366 --> 00:55:51,026
- Sir?
- Are you giving me an eye test?

808
00:55:51,666 --> 00:55:54,036
You're fast, but why have there been
so many typos recently?

809
00:55:54,036 --> 00:55:55,136
I'm sorry, sir.

810
00:55:57,966 --> 00:56:00,706
I know Director Park Tae Won at Juplus.
Want an introduction?

811
00:56:01,236 --> 00:56:02,476
I would really appreciate that.

812
00:56:03,346 --> 00:56:06,846
- Tuesday. The highlight of my week.
- Because of the black bean noodles?

813
00:56:06,916 --> 00:56:09,286
It's better than most Chinese restaurants.

814
00:56:09,346 --> 00:56:11,886
I heard the Friday special
at the Shinpyeong Daily is beef bone soup.

815
00:56:13,786 --> 00:56:14,786
Hello?

816
00:56:15,726 --> 00:56:18,356
Looks like she's got a boyfriend.

817
00:56:19,496 --> 00:56:21,496
The caller ID says
"Manager Kim, Self-Reliance Center."

818
00:56:23,196 --> 00:56:26,536
He knows the exact date
you were brought to Minjin Church.

819
00:56:26,896 --> 00:56:29,836
How old is he?

820
00:56:30,266 --> 00:56:32,776
He was born in 1968.
His name is Kim Gwang Cheol.

821
00:56:33,376 --> 00:56:34,536
If he's your biological father,

822
00:56:34,976 --> 00:56:38,006
then you were never Geum Ba Ra,
but Kim Ba Ra all along.

823
00:56:48,016 --> 00:56:51,056
I heard from Manager Kim
at the Self-Reliance Center.

824
00:56:51,656 --> 00:56:53,526
My name is Geum Ba Ra.

825
00:56:54,756 --> 00:56:55,966
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

826
00:57:14,446 --> 00:57:16,016
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

827
00:57:26,526 --> 00:57:27,526
Hello?

828
00:57:27,596 --> 00:57:30,226
(Just got your text.)

829
00:57:31,396 --> 00:57:32,396
Hello.

830
00:57:32,566 --> 00:57:35,436
(From the center...)

831
00:57:35,466 --> 00:57:37,336
(You live in Seoul?)

832
00:57:37,336 --> 00:57:38,336
Yes.

833
00:57:38,866 --> 00:57:42,906
(When are you free?
I'm available right now.)

834
00:57:43,106 --> 00:57:46,346
(Just tell me where, and I'll head over.)

835
00:57:47,016 --> 00:57:49,216
(It won't take me more than an hour.)

836
00:57:57,686 --> 00:57:59,656
Does the ER have an orthopedist?

837
00:59:36,626 --> 00:59:38,026
(Kim Gwang Cheol)

838
00:59:57,606 --> 00:59:58,646
Geum Ba Ra?

839
01:00:11,326 --> 01:00:14,856
December 21, 1999,

840
01:00:15,196 --> 01:00:16,366
at Minjin Church?

841
01:00:16,966 --> 01:00:17,966
Yes.

842
01:00:19,636 --> 01:00:20,936
Are you ready to order?

843
01:00:21,266 --> 01:00:22,266
Coffee.

844
01:00:22,566 --> 01:00:23,666
An Americano?

845
01:00:24,106 --> 01:00:26,036
- Yes.
- Hot?

846
01:00:26,106 --> 01:00:27,306
No, iced.

847
01:00:28,376 --> 01:00:29,376
I'll have the same.

848
01:00:33,216 --> 01:00:36,246
I looked into it,
and on that day, two babies...

849
01:00:37,046 --> 01:00:38,046
Yes...

850
01:01:23,126 --> 01:01:25,966
(Doctor Shin)

851
01:01:26,096 --> 01:01:28,366
When will you stop being so formal?
It's going to become a habit.

852
01:01:28,566 --> 01:01:29,866
It'll become a habit.

853
01:01:29,866 --> 01:01:32,066
Reporter Geum
is going to be devastated. This is awful.

854
01:01:32,336 --> 01:01:34,476
- What are we going to do?
- Are you sure about this?

855
01:01:34,536 --> 01:01:36,406
But you know how people
can have a change of heart.

856
01:01:36,906 --> 01:01:40,446
- Having second thoughts?
- I can have you all fired! Hey, Lee Shim!

857
01:01:40,516 --> 01:01:42,446
- Park Soo!
- You want me to be honest?

858
01:01:42,516 --> 01:01:44,286
You should be,
especially with a good drink like this.

859
01:01:44,346 --> 01:01:46,156
Don't you know what people look for
in a marriage prospect?

860
01:01:46,156 --> 01:01:48,086
I don't. All I know is love.

861
01:01:48,156 --> 01:01:50,886
- Have you actually said "I love you?"
- Of course I've been in love.

862
01:01:50,956 --> 01:01:54,226
If you get adopted,
that lady won't volunteer anymore, right?

863
01:01:54,356 --> 01:01:55,496
She said she'd keep coming.

864
01:01:55,496 --> 01:01:57,726
Think it through so you have no regrets.

865
01:01:57,726 --> 01:01:59,636
- I won't.
- I was away at "school" all this time.

866
01:01:59,636 --> 01:02:00,796
You know what I mean by "school," right?

867
01:02:01,036 --> 01:02:02,396
- Kim Jin Ju.
- Yes?

868
01:02:02,396 --> 01:02:03,836
Ever think about getting on
an operating table?

869
01:02:04,466 --> 01:02:08,406
I don't know who'll be the first
to read this, but...

870
01:02:08,706 --> 01:02:10,006
What do you think of me?

871
01:02:10,006 --> 01:02:12,446
Not as chairman of the orphanage
or the hospital director,

872
01:02:12,506 --> 01:02:15,646
- but just as a man?
- I couldn't possibly...
